JQuery Callback Functions

•	A callback is a function you pass to another function.
•	It gets called (executed) automatically when the main task is done.
•	Why? jQuery operations (like hiding/showing elements or loading data) are often asynchronous—they don't block the rest of your code
•	Without callbacks, your code might run too early and cause errors.
With callback
Sytnax:- $(selector).hide(speed,callback);

$(document).ready(function(){
  $("button").click(function(){
    $("p").hide("slow", function(){
      alert("The paragraph is now hidden");
    });
  });
});

WITHOUT CALLBACK
$(document).ready(function(){
  $("button").click(function(){
    $("p").hide(1000);
    alert("The paragraph is now hidden");
  });
});
 jQuery Chaining
 run multiple actions (methods) on the same element(s) in a single line of code. It's like a "chain" where each method returns the jQuery object, so you can keep calling more methods without selecting the element again. 

WHY WE USE CHAINING?

•	Efficiency: No need to repeat selectors (like $('#id')) multiple times.
•	Readability: One line shows the full sequence of actions.
•	Performance: jQuery handles it smoothly under the hood.

BASIC SYNTAX :-
$(selector).method1().method2().method3();

jQuery DOM Manipulation
One very important part of jQuery is the possibility to manipulate the DOM.
jQuery comes with a bunch of DOM related methods that make it easy to access and manipulate elements and attributes.
DOM = Document Object Model

The DOM defines a standard for accessing HTML and XML documents:

text(), html(), and val()
•	text() - Sets or returns the text content of selected elements
•	html() - Sets or returns the content of selected elements (including HTML markup)
•	val() - Sets or returns the value of form fields.
•	attr() :- attr() method is used to get attribute values.
text() Method
$(document).ready(function(){
  $("#btn1").click(function(){
    alert("Text: " + $("#test").text());
  });
html() Method

  $("#btn2").click(function(){
    alert("HTML: " + $("#test").html());
  });
})
val() Method
$(document).ready(function(){
  $("button").click(function(){
    alert("Value: " + $("#test").val());
  });
});
attr() Method
$(document).ready(function(){
  $("button").click(function(){
    alert($("#w3s").attr("href"));
  });
});










